(42, 'Twitter initiates talks with tech companies over sale: source', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/twitter-moving-closer-sale-possible-suitors-salesforce-google-131713271--finance.html"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/xD3Z9aEu9hU4.pfqOhOm0w--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-09-23T131713Z_1006950001_LYNXNPEC8M0SN_RTROPTP_2_CBUSINESS-US-TWITTER-M-A.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="People holding mobile phones are silhouetted against a backdrop projected with the Twitter logo in Warsaw" align="left" title="People holding mobile phones are silhouetted against a backdrop projected with the Twitter logo in Warsaw" border="0" /></a>A sale of Twitter has been the subject of on-again, off-again rumors for many months as the company grapples with stagnant user growth, soft advertising sales and losses running at hundreds of millions of dollars a year. CNBC, citing anonymous sources, reported on Friday that Twitter is in talks with companies including Google and may receive a formal bid soon. Twitter and Alphabet Inc, Google&#039;s parent company did not respond to a request for comment.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 22:52:33', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/twitter-moving-closer-sale-possible-suitors-salesforce-google-131713271--finance.html', '', 2),
(43, 'SpaceX blast investigation suggests breach in oxygen tank\'s helium system', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/spacex-blast-investigation-suggests-breach-oxygen-tanks-helium-174748954--finance.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/35Z_LyB0rAOOLsYrlV.MDg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-09-23T175040Z_1006990002_LYNXNPEC8M167_RTROPTP_2_CTECH-US-SPACEX-BLAST.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="File photo of an explosion on the launch site of a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket is shown in this still image from video in Cape Canaveral" align="left" title="File photo of an explosion on the launch site of a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket is shown in this still image from video in Cape Canaveral" border="0" /></a>By Irene Klotz DALLAS (Reuters) - A SpaceX rocket that burst into flames on its launch pad ate the beginning of this month likely suffered a large breach in its upper-stage helium system, the company said on Friday. SpaceX, owned and operated by technology entrepreneur Elon Musk, was fueling a Falcon 9 rocket on the launch pad in Florida on Sept. 1 in preparation for a routine test-firing when a bright fireball suddenly emerged around the rocket&#039;s upper stage. &quot;At this stage of the investigation, preliminary review of the data and debris suggests that a large breach in the cryogenic helium system of the second stage liquid oxygen tank took place,&quot; SpaceX said in a statement posted on its website.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 19:15:48', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/spacex-blast-investigation-suggests-breach-oxygen-tanks-helium-174748954--finance.html', '', 2),
(44, 'Facebook apologizes for overstating key ad metric', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/facebook-apologizes-overstating-key-ad-metric-202907652--finance.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/jpbmObVCUa_7xEJgFbxuSQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-09-23T202907Z_1006990001_LYNXNPEC8M1CF_RTROPTP_2_CTECH-US-FACEBOOK-ADVERTISING.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="A man poses with a magnifier in front of a Facebook logo on display in this illustration taken in Sarajevo" align="left" title="A man poses with a magnifier in front of a Facebook logo on display in this illustration taken in Sarajevo" border="0" /></a>(Reuters) - Facebook Inc on Friday apologized for an error in the way it measured a key metric of video viewership that significantly amplified users&#039; viewing times on its platform. At the time, Facebook had said that the &quot;discrepancy&quot; did not impact advertising billings and introduced newer metrics to replace the previous method. Facebook has made a significant strides into video, which has attracted significant advertising interest and has benefited from the shift in advertising spending toward the internet and other mobile platforms.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 20:29:07', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/facebook-apologizes-overstating-key-ad-metric-202907652--finance.html', '', 2),
(45, 'IBM, China UnionPay complete block chain pilot project on bank loyalty points', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/ibm-china-unionpay-complete-block-chain-pilot-project-195216906--sector.html"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/GtDNfR43aGUGWiKCZdsupw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-09-23T195216Z_1006950001_LYNXNPEC8M1BL_RTROPTP_2_CBUSINESS-US-IBM-CHINA-BLOCKCHAIN.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="The logo of Dow Jones Industrial Average stock market index listed company IBM (IBM) is seen in Los Angeles" align="left" title="The logo of Dow Jones Industrial Average stock market index listed company IBM (IBM) is seen in Los Angeles" border="0" /></a>IBM said on Friday it completed a pilot project with Chinese credit card company China UnionPay that will facilitate the sharing of loyalty bonus points among banks using block chain technology. Bonus points earned through purchases on bank cards have long been an effective tool to attract and encourage customers to use specific cards. IBM&#039;s collaboration with China UnionPay will enable consumers worldwide to exchange bonus points from their various banks in less than a minute to select rewards they want.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 19:52:16', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/ibm-china-unionpay-complete-block-chain-pilot-project-195216906--sector.html', '', 2),
(46, 'Exclusive: Japan\'s antitrust watchdog considers action against Apple, carriers - sources', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/exclusive-japans-antitrust-watchdog-considers-action-against-apple-100710199--finance.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/7gknsoytDpVqc2V6S2YpWw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-09-23T100710Z_1_LYNXNPEC8M0JN_RTROPTP_2_APPLE-IPHONE-JAPAN.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="Shimizu tries an Apple Watch Series 2 after it went on sale at the Apple Store at Tokyo&#039;s Omotesando shopping district" align="left" title="Shimizu tries an Apple Watch Series 2 after it went on sale at the Apple Store at Tokyo&#039;s Omotesando shopping district" border="0" /></a>By Yoshiyasu Shida TOKYO (Reuters) - Japanese regulators are considering taking action against Apple Inc over possible antitrust violations that may have helped it dominate the nation&#039;s smartphone sales, government sources said, a move that could hit the company&#039;s profit margins in one of its most profitable markets. In a report published last month, Japan&#039;s Fair Trade Commission (FTC) said that NTT Docomo, KDDI Corp and Softbank Group were refusing to sell older surplus iPhone models to third party retailers, thereby hobbling smaller competitors. Apple was not named in that report, but two senior government sources told Reuters that regulators were also focusing on Apple&#039;s supply agreements with all three carriers.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 10:07:10', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/exclusive-japans-antitrust-watchdog-considers-action-against-apple-100710199--finance.html', '', 2),
(47, 'Connecticut becoming a hub for new bioscience companies', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/connecticut-becoming-hub-bioscience-companies-145315820.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/wPHtUILDyV2fvRl01Z0DEg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://globalfinance.zenfs.com/images/US_AHTTP_AP_FINANCIALTIMES/885df7daf9ba44e1b0d83aa93cce95c5_original.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Connecticut becoming a hub for new bioscience companies" align="left" title="Connecticut becoming a hub for new bioscience companies" border="0" /></a>Connecticut hasn&#039;t become the Silicon Valley of bioscience quite yet, but five years after lawmakers made a massive investment to support the development of that industry, there is a thriving hub in Farmington. ...</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 14:56:53', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/connecticut-becoming-hub-bioscience-companies-145315820.html', '', 2),
(48, 'Everything coming to Netflix, Amazon Prime, and HBO Now in October', '<p><a href="http://www.theverge.com/2016/9/24/13035574/netflix-amazon-prime-hbo-now-new-movies-tv-shows-october-2016"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/GT9e6bL3_w58m_kgReN09g--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_US/News/The%20Verge/a1268db51bfda1963a841806b041ed616517d4f0920bcf4564c11d9c425df749_2040.0.0.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Everything coming to Netflix, Amazon Prime, and HBO Now in October" align="left" title="Everything coming to Netflix, Amazon Prime, and HBO Now in October" border="0" /></a>John P. Johnson / HBO</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 14:00:03', '0', 0, 0, 'http://www.theverge.com/2016/9/24/13035574/netflix-amazon-prime-hbo-now-new-movies-tv-shows-october-2016', '', 2),
(49, 'Which smart bulbs should you use with Alexa?', '<p><a href="http://www.cnet.com/news/which-smart-bulbs-should-you-use-with-alexa/"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/9oTLRH1L6RXEwYQIUZ5WQg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en-US/homerun/cnet.cbs.com/96428984c19c83c0d65c34fe757ec67d" width="130" height="86" alt="Which smart bulbs should you use with Alexa?" align="left" title="Which smart bulbs should you use with Alexa?" border="0" /></a>Amazon&#039;s voice-activated virtual assistant can control a growing number of smart lights. If you&#039;re wondering which ones are the best fit for your home, we&#039;re here to help.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 12:00:13', '0', 0, 0, 'http://www.cnet.com/news/which-smart-bulbs-should-you-use-with-alexa/', '', 2),
(50, 'Trim your wireless bill -- skip that phone upgrade', '<p><a href="http://www.cnet.com/news/trim-your-wireless-bill-skip-that-phone-upgrade/"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/kGriTMA.wmvigcT.5UpGeg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en-US/homerun/cnet.cbs.com/3ce901d3d86671d6b9de29d1dc92859a" width="130" height="86" alt="Trim your wireless bill -- skip that phone upgrade" align="left" title="Trim your wireless bill -- skip that phone upgrade" border="0" /></a>In this edition of Ask Maggie, CNET&#039;s Marguerite Reardon explains why wireless customers should resist the temptation to get a new phone every two years.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 12:00:10', '0', 0, 0, 'http://www.cnet.com/news/trim-your-wireless-bill-skip-that-phone-upgrade/', '', 2),
(51, 'Facebook or Twitter for the presidential debate? You want to agree or argue?', '<p><a href="http://www.cnet.com/news/facebook-twitter-presidential-debate-donald-trump-hillary-clinton-live-stream/"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/gTCz0svmfbgZrdgWZjXwng--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en-US/homerun/cnet.cbs.com/e3b1508aeabb0c56923c2bc5b286d1b9" width="130" height="86" alt="Facebook or Twitter for the presidential debate? You want to agree or argue?" align="left" title="Facebook or Twitter for the presidential debate? You want to agree or argue?" border="0" /></a>The debates will be the same on both social networks, but the comments? Not so much.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 12:00:07', '0', 0, 0, 'http://www.cnet.com/news/facebook-twitter-presidential-debate-donald-trump-hillary-clinton-live-stream/', '', 2),
