(107, '15,000 march in Helsinki anti-racism protest', '<p><a href="https://news.yahoo.com/15-000-march-helsinki-anti-racism-protest-135618886.html"><img src="https://s1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/hA4q68XDeCqj08tqDOhlmw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/4bc6432af0848640d25400a92573d7a304cab9a7.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Participants demonstrate against racism and fascism in Helsinki, Finland on September 24, 2016" align="left" title="Participants demonstrate against racism and fascism in Helsinki, Finland on September 24, 2016" border="0" /></a>Around 15,000 people marched in central Helsinki Saturday to protest against rising racism and violent right-wing extremism, police said, following the recent death of a man allegedly attacked by a neo-Nazi leader. Helsinki police tweeted that around 15,000 people were taking part in the protest, while thousands attended other demonstrations around the country, including Prime Minister Juha Sipila who joined a march in the central town of Kuopio. Several much smaller counter-demonstrations were also held in Helsinki, but police kept the groups separated and no clashes were reported.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 13:56:18', '0', 0, 0, 'https://news.yahoo.com/15-000-march-helsinki-anti-racism-protest-135618886.html', '', 3),
(108, 'Paul Pogba scores first goal for Man Utd', '<p><a href="https://news.yahoo.com/paul-pogba-scores-first-goal-man-utd-003456857--sow.html"><img src="https://s1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/haxINnv9T9v.eSNmkjdBqQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/e9b54b1d853e0805f7c22eb339e5f3bbfe61989d.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Manchester United&#039;s French midfielder Paul Pogba (2L) heads his side&#039;s fourth goal against Leicester City at Old Trafford in Manchester, north-west England, on September 24, 2016" align="left" title="Manchester United&#039;s French midfielder Paul Pogba (2L) heads his side&#039;s fourth goal against Leicester City at Old Trafford in Manchester, north-west England, on September 24, 2016" border="0" /></a>Paul Pogba finally ended his wait for a first goal for Manchester United since his world record transfer in Saturday&#039;s 4-1 win against Leicester. Timing his run perfectly, Pogba met Daley Blind&#039;s corner with a powerful header that gave Leicester goalkeeper Ron-Robert Zieler no chance. It was United&#039;s fourth goal of the half as Jose Mourinho&#039;s side demolished the Premier League champions.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 13:55:05', '0', 0, 0, 'https://news.yahoo.com/paul-pogba-scores-first-goal-man-utd-003456857--sow.html', '', 3),
(109, 'Corbyn re-elected as UK Labour leader after bitter fight', '<p><a href="https://news.yahoo.com/socialist-corbyn-heads-victory-over-divided-labour-033129939.html"><img src="https://s.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/qqqHmwLk.mVpi_MWKklkOQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/e1c78a68f072f36099137e708a7c8b0fd938a6e7.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="British opposition Labour Party leader Jeremy Corbyn after being announced as the winner of the party&#039;s leadership contest at the Labour Party Leadership Conference in Liverpool on September 24, 2016" align="left" title="British opposition Labour Party leader Jeremy Corbyn after being announced as the winner of the party&#039;s leadership contest at the Labour Party Leadership Conference in Liverpool on September 24, 2016" border="0" /></a>Left-winger Jeremy Corbyn was re-elected British Labour leader on Saturday, seeing off a challenge from MPs but leaving the opposition party split as critics said it was even further from power than before. Supporters in Liverpool, northwest England, leapt to their feet cheering as the 67-year-old was confirmed winner with 61.8 percent of the vote among party members and supporters, easily defeating rival MP Owen Smith. In his acceptance speech, Corbyn urged unity, pledging to &quot;wipe the slate clean&quot; after accusations of bullying by supporters and fears of an irreparable breach between left-wingers and centrists.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 13:45:24', '0', 0, 0, 'https://news.yahoo.com/socialist-corbyn-heads-victory-over-divided-labour-033129939.html', '', 3),
