(139, 'Syria\'s Aleppo reels from new wave of air strikes', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/strikes-kill-least-25-civilians-syrias-aleppo-monitor-092911282.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/eLmb6wACpLsQG8AxVbKM3Q--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/0fa6922f59cfc58cd11e14904f690832ec386030.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="A Syrian boy awaits treatment at a make-shift hospital following air strikes on rebel-held eastern areas of Aleppo on September 24, 2016" align="left" title="A Syrian boy awaits treatment at a make-shift hospital following air strikes on rebel-held eastern areas of Aleppo on September 24, 2016" border="0" /></a>Residents in Syria&#039;s battleground city of Aleppo cowered indoors Saturday as fierce air strikes toppled buildings and killed at least 32 civilians, after diplomatic efforts to revive a ceasefire failed. Nearly two million civilians were without water in the devastated northern city after regime bombardment damaged a pumping station and rebels shut down another in retaliation, the United Nations said. Rebel-held districts in east Aleppo came under intense air and artillery fire for a fifth night as the army prepared a ground offensive to recapture the whole of the divided city.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 14:46:30', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/strikes-kill-least-25-civilians-syrias-aleppo-monitor-092911282.html', '', 4),
(140, 'Pope urges \'sincere dialogue\' as he meets Nice attack victims', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/pope-urges-sincere-dialogue-meets-nice-attack-victims-130456155.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/urZ9CvePKARIBe5hBskSiA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/1c9dcf5163f1a247e075fef8ec1758aa5d79ecea.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Pope Francis blesses a woman as he meets with survivors and relatives of the victims of the July 14 Nice attack in the Paul VI hall at the Vatican on September 24, 2016" align="left" title="Pope Francis blesses a woman as he meets with survivors and relatives of the victims of the July 14 Nice attack in the Paul VI hall at the Vatican on September 24, 2016" border="0" /></a>Pope Francis on Saturday called for a &quot;sincere dialogue&quot; between Christians and Muslims as he met grieving relatives and survivors of France&#039;s Bastille Day attack, in which a jihadist ploughed his truck into a crowd. &quot;The Muslim presence here today was indispensable,&quot; he said.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 14:40:12', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/pope-urges-sincere-dialogue-meets-nice-attack-victims-130456155.html', '', 4),
(141, 'Polish doctors hit streets demanding higher wages', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/polish-doctors-hit-streets-demanding-higher-wages-143817573.html"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/KnqfUYwKZ17xf.NLQA5zYg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/3299c9315c918000b19e9ed4924373eb37791845.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Polish doctors and health professionals take part in a demonstration on September 24, 2016 demanding more finance support for public health services" align="left" title="Polish doctors and health professionals take part in a demonstration on September 24, 2016 demanding more finance support for public health services" border="0" /></a>Thousands of doctors, nurses and hospital workers marched through central Warsaw Saturday demanding Poland&#039;s rightwing government spend more on public health, especially to hike notoriously low salaries. &quot;After six years of studies and a thirteen-month internship, I earn 2,200 zloty (510 euros, $580) per month,&quot; young doctor Bartlomiej Kolodziejczyk told AFP. Protesters are demanding that Poland&#039;s populist Law and Justice (PiS) government immediately hike health spending to 6.8 percent of GDP as recommended by the World Health Organization.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 14:38:17', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/polish-doctors-hit-streets-demanding-higher-wages-143817573.html', '', 4),
(142, 'Colombia set to sign historic peace deal', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/colombia-sign-historic-peace-deal-100030451.html"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/K0jPeVqT2M5uLUxYep0q8w--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/82d3870c150ebec48e88338459d96421f2ec0c14.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Members of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) attend the announcement of the approval of the peace deal with the government during the 10th National Guerrilla Conference in Llanos del Yari, Colombia, on September 23, 2016" align="left" title="Members of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) attend the announcement of the approval of the peace deal with the government during the 10th National Guerrilla Conference in Llanos del Yari, Colombia, on September 23, 2016" border="0" /></a>Colombia will turn the page on a half-century conflict that has stained its modern history with blood when the FARC rebels and the government sign a peace deal on Monday. President Juan Manuel Santos and the leader of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC), Rodrigo Londono -- better known by his nom de guerre, Timoleon &quot;Timochenko&quot; Jimenez -- are set to sign the accord at 5:00 pm (2200 GMT) in a ceremony in the colorful colonial city of Cartagena on the Caribbean coast. It will be preceded by a tribute to the Colombian military and police, presided over by Santos, and a prayer for peace and reconciliation at an 18th century Catholic church in Cartagena&#039;s old town.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 14:27:15', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/colombia-sign-historic-peace-deal-100030451.html', '', 4),
(143, '15,000 march in Helsinki anti-racism protest', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/15-000-march-helsinki-anti-racism-protest-135618886.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/hA4q68XDeCqj08tqDOhlmw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/4bc6432af0848640d25400a92573d7a304cab9a7.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Participants demonstrate against racism and fascism in Helsinki, Finland on September 24, 2016" align="left" title="Participants demonstrate against racism and fascism in Helsinki, Finland on September 24, 2016" border="0" /></a>Around 15,000 people marched in central Helsinki Saturday to protest against rising racism and violent right-wing extremism, police said, following the recent death of a man allegedly attacked by a neo-Nazi leader. Helsinki police tweeted that around 15,000 people were taking part in the protest, while thousands attended other demonstrations around the country, including Prime Minister Juha Sipila who joined a march in the central town of Kuopio. Several much smaller counter-demonstrations were also held in Helsinki, but police kept the groups separated and no clashes were reported.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 13:56:18', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/15-000-march-helsinki-anti-racism-protest-135618886.html', '', 4),
(144, 'Corbyn re-elected as UK Labour leader after bitter fight', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/socialist-corbyn-heads-victory-over-divided-labour-033129939.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/qqqHmwLk.mVpi_MWKklkOQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/e1c78a68f072f36099137e708a7c8b0fd938a6e7.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="British opposition Labour Party leader Jeremy Corbyn after being announced as the winner of the party&#039;s leadership contest at the Labour Party Leadership Conference in Liverpool on September 24, 2016" align="left" title="British opposition Labour Party leader Jeremy Corbyn after being announced as the winner of the party&#039;s leadership contest at the Labour Party Leadership Conference in Liverpool on September 24, 2016" border="0" /></a>Left-winger Jeremy Corbyn was re-elected British Labour leader on Saturday, seeing off a challenge from MPs but leaving the opposition party split as critics said it was even further from power than before. Supporters in Liverpool, northwest England, leapt to their feet cheering as the 67-year-old was confirmed winner with 61.8 percent of the vote among party members and supporters, easily defeating rival MP Owen Smith. In his acceptance speech, Corbyn urged unity, pledging to &quot;wipe the slate clean&quot; after accusations of bullying by supporters and fears of an irreparable breach between left-wingers and centrists.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 13:45:24', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/socialist-corbyn-heads-victory-over-divided-labour-033129939.html', '', 4),
(145, 'UN, AU, EU appeal for calm in DR Congo', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/un-au-eu-appeal-calm-dr-congo-133337682.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/SeYGCw9pMvGUeS3zuQKl_w--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/f1f37e142582fad8dc9626a88611c6671fab41bd.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Demonstrators gather in front of a burning car during an opposition rally in Kinshasa on September 19, 2016" align="left" title="Demonstrators gather in front of a burning car during an opposition rally in Kinshasa on September 19, 2016" border="0" /></a>The United Nations, African Union, European Union and a fourth international organization made a joint appeal on Saturday to the government and opposition in the Democratic Republic of Congo to exercise restraint amid violent political unrest. The three main international bodies were joined by the 57 International Organization of La Francophonie, which held a high-profile summit in Kinshasa in 2012.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 13:33:37', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/un-au-eu-appeal-calm-dr-congo-133337682.html', '', 4),
(146, 'Corbyn: earthy leftwing leader who splits UK\'s Labour', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/corbyn-earthy-leftwing-leader-splits-uks-labour-114255080.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/IZbi818L.Htaz.nj59MuXg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/77d34f66356204a7c55c50cf440229d0682c793b.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="British opposition Labour Party leader Jeremy Corbyn reacts after being announced as the winner of the party&#039;s leadership contest in Liverpool on September 24, 2016" align="left" title="British opposition Labour Party leader Jeremy Corbyn reacts after being announced as the winner of the party&#039;s leadership contest in Liverpool on September 24, 2016" border="0" /></a>Opposed by most of his MPs and lionised by grassroots activists, socialist Jeremy Corbyn was re-elected Saturday as leader of Britain&#039;s opposition Labour, but takes his party into an increasingly uncertain future. Corbyn spent decades on the backbenches of parliament, where his left-wing views have long been out of fashion, before his surprise election as Labour leader last September. Rumbling criticism of his leadership style turned into open rebellion after June&#039;s referendum vote to leave the European Union, which critics say Corbyn did not do enough to prevent, but he refused to stand aside.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 11:42:55', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/corbyn-earthy-leftwing-leader-splits-uks-labour-114255080.html', '', 4),
(147, 'Beleaguered Merkel meets Balkan leaders over migrants', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/wounded-merkel-meets-balkan-leaders-over-migrants-035138297.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/TTs_mjFfLE5ghXMUJDgNwA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/5975cab4109e136dcd83e775eb6e8da4fefa0fec.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="German Chancellor Angela Merkel has pledged there would be no repeat of last year&#039;s &quot;chaotic&quot; border opening to refugees" align="left" title="German Chancellor Angela Merkel has pledged there would be no repeat of last year&#039;s &quot;chaotic&quot; border opening to refugees" border="0" /></a>German Chancellor Angela Merkel, hurt by a string of dismal election results over her refugees policy, was in Vienna Saturday for talks with leaders of countries along the Balkan migrant route. Austrian Chancellor Christian Kern said that the aim of the talks, also attended by top EU officials, was to &quot;accelerate&quot; momentum towards ending Europe&#039;s worst migration crisis since 1945. &quot;At the moment there is a range of individual measures but no common European line,&quot; Kern told the Kleine Zeitung daily.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 11:17:52', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/wounded-merkel-meets-balkan-leaders-over-migrants-035138297.html', '', 4),
(148, 'Third deadly drone strike in a week hits Yemen Qaeda', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/third-deadly-drone-strike-week-hits-yemen-qaeda-110258819.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/4Ln9qkmv6kO0A3zBDtceZA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/Part-WAS-Was8974857-1-1-0.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="The United States is the only government to operate drones over Yemen but only sporadically releases statements on its long-running bombing campaign against the country&#039;s powerful Al-Qaeda branch" align="left" title="The United States is the only government to operate drones over Yemen but only sporadically releases statements on its long-running bombing campaign against the country&#039;s powerful Al-Qaeda branch" border="0" /></a>Aden (AFP) - An apparent US drone strike has killed five suspected Al-Qaeda members in Yemen in the third such attack this week, a security official said on Saturday.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 11:02:58', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/third-deadly-drone-strike-week-hits-yemen-qaeda-110258819.html', '', 4),
(149, 'Can a Police-Misconduct Lawsuit Lead to Reform?', 'Last week, the lawyer representing the family of Sandra Bland, a black woman who died in a Waller County, Texas, jail last year, announced the settlement of a wrongful-death lawsuit with state and county officials. As with other highly visible cases, the settlement garnered mixed reaction. Some critics saw it as an attempt by the county to buy the family’s silence, while others appeared to fault the family for bringing a lawsuit from which they could receive compensation for their personal tragedy.', '2016-09-24 11:00:00', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/police-misconduct-lawsuit-lead-reform-110000638.html', '', 4),
(150, 'Heavy security in tense Gabon after Bongo re-election validated', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/gabon-court-upholds-president-ali-bongos-election-win-005553969.html"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/hDtRgwUNfF2ujkOohzguQA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/b8ef8ee4bd7459b5bcc08ebf78897cd5ab0aa081.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Gabonese security forces deployed next to a campaign poster of President Ali Bongo in Libreville on September 23, 2016" align="left" title="Gabonese security forces deployed next to a campaign poster of President Ali Bongo in Libreville on September 23, 2016" border="0" /></a>Libreville&#039;s nearly empty streets were under the watch of a heavy police and military presence on Saturday after Gabon&#039;s top court upheld President Ali Bongo&#039;s re-election in bitterly disputed polls. The Constitutional Court, while partially changing the results of the close August 27 vote, said Bongo maintained a lead over his former ally-turned-opponent Jean Ping, at a televised public hearing overnight Friday-Saturday. Bongo took 50.66 percent of the vote against 47.24 percent for Ping, the court ruled, putting his margin at 11,000 -- higher than the less than 6,000 initially announced.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 09:47:21', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/gabon-court-upholds-president-ali-bongos-election-win-005553969.html', '', 4),
(151, 'Gun, suicide bomb attacks kill 12 in Iraq\'s Tikrit', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/gun-suicide-bomb-attacks-kill-12-iraqs-tikrit-085743659.html"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/f1jEM3VmalInui2BcAbsoA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/Part-NIC-Nic499416-1-1-0.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Tikrit, located 160 kilometres (100 miles) north of Baghdad, was the second city to fall to IS in 2014 as the jihadists swept through large areas north and west of the capital" align="left" title="Tikrit, located 160 kilometres (100 miles) north of Baghdad, was the second city to fall to IS in 2014 as the jihadists swept through large areas north and west of the capital" border="0" /></a>Militants killed 12 people in a shooting and a suicide bombing Saturday in the northern city of Tikrit, which was recaptured from the Islamic State group last year, police said. Tikrit was seized by IS in June 2014, but the city has largely been spared the attacks that have plagued other parts of the country since its recapture. There was no immediate claim of responsibility for the attacks, but IS frequently carries out suicide attacks targeting both civilians and security forces in Iraq.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 09:41:48', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/gun-suicide-bomb-attacks-kill-12-iraqs-tikrit-085743659.html', '', 4),
(152, 'North Korea air show thumbs nose at sanctions', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/north-korea-air-show-thumbs-nose-sanctions-061445315--finance.html"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/9S1tfH8IaUYXWH3blMBwdQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/ceed023196d428f00eb78921bdf8d5a226af5f23.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="A North Korean soldier watches as Hughes MD-500 helicopters perform a fly-by during the first Wonsan Friendship Air Festival" align="left" title="A North Korean soldier watches as Hughes MD-500 helicopters perform a fly-by during the first Wonsan Friendship Air Festival" border="0" /></a>Just weeks after carrying out its fifth nuclear test, North Korea put on an unprecedented civilian and military air force display Saturday at the country&#039;s first ever public aviation show. The two-day Wonsan International Friendship Air Festival was held at the newly refurbished Kalma Airport -- previously a military airfield -- completed last year to boost tourism in the area around the eastern port city of Wonsan. The festival was already scheduled before North Korea conducted its fifth nuclear test on September 9, triggering international outrage and threats of still further sanctions against the deeply isolated nuclear-armed country.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 08:58:47', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/north-korea-air-show-thumbs-nose-sanctions-061445315--finance.html', '', 4),
(153, 'Syrian, Russian aircraft pound rebel-held Aleppo', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/syrian-russian-aircraft-pound-rebel-held-aleppo-084002990.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/fb4HzDQrdkg5nPh1JjA4QQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/c57ba426efac1cb2bfed2a8c4a394d8bcc3ed5f4.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="A Syrian family stands in the rubble following a reported airstrike on the al-Muasalat area in the northern Syrian city of Aleppo on September 23, 2016" align="left" title="A Syrian family stands in the rubble following a reported airstrike on the al-Muasalat area in the northern Syrian city of Aleppo on September 23, 2016" border="0" /></a>Residents in rebel-held areas of Syria&#039;s Aleppo cowered in their homes on Saturday as relentless missile strikes and barrel bomb attacks pounded the besieged eastern half of the divided city. Heavy bombardment on Friday killed at least 47 people, among them seven children, the Britain-based Syrian Observatory for Human Rights monitor said. &quot;There are certainly deaths in the bombing (on Saturday) but we don&#039;t have tolls yet and people are still trapped under the rubble,&quot; said Observatory director Rami Abdel Rahman.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 08:40:02', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/syrian-russian-aircraft-pound-rebel-held-aleppo-084002990.html', '', 4),
(154, 'Tennis - Wozniacki battles into Tokyo final', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/tennis-wozniacki-battles-tokyo-final-073928519.html"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/5HGWp_pUObFv8QvZaCYI3Q--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/a355104764997f724871e15d044e1c4d56b6f4c7.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Tennis - Wozniacki battles into Tokyo final" align="left" title="Tennis - Wozniacki battles into Tokyo final" border="0" /></a>- Former world number one Caroline Wozniacki produced a spirited fightback to beat fourth seed Agnieszka Radwanska 4-6, 7-5, 6-4 and reach the Pan Pacific Open final on Saturday. The Dane will face either Ukrainian Elina Svitolina, or Japan&#039;s Naomi Osaka in Sunday&#039;s Tokyo final. Wozniacki&#039;s gritty display will give her confidence a further lift after battling back from injuries this year to reach the US Open semi-finals earlier this month. Despite coughing up the first set on a double fault, Wozniacki showed glimpses of her old form in an error-strewn match featuring 13 breaks of serve. ...</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 07:39:28', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/tennis-wozniacki-battles-tokyo-final-073928519.html', '', 4),
(155, 'The US presidential debate: what you need to know', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/us-presidential-debate-know-071725708.html"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/feqeHhnbLY1pw69vdpxoKg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/Part-GTY-505438262-1-1-1.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Lester Holt (L), pictured with Andrea Mitchell at the Democratic candidates debate in January, will moderate the first presidential debate" align="left" title="Lester Holt (L), pictured with Andrea Mitchell at the Democratic candidates debate in January, will moderate the first presidential debate" border="0" /></a>Monday&#039;s US presidential debate, a combat of titans pitting the Democrat Hillary Clinton against the Republican Donald Trump, is sure to be a major moment in the campaign, with just six weeks left before the November 8 election. The debate could break all records for a US political audience, given the sharply contrasting personalities -- and positions -- of Trump and Clinton. Hofstra is no newcomer to presidential debates, having hosted them in 2008 and 2012.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 07:17:25', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/us-presidential-debate-know-071725708.html', '', 4),
(156, 'As debaters, Trump and Clinton both have strengths and weaknesses', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/debaters-trump-clinton-both-strengths-weaknesses-070946170.html"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/tmaz.LNqud4WMUsUsIagMQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/67326103cc4b969170da6b9f76eeb3c99abab630.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="No candidate in this campaign has matched Donald Trump&#039;s ability to electrify crowds of thousands" align="left" title="No candidate in this campaign has matched Donald Trump&#039;s ability to electrify crowds of thousands" border="0" /></a>Neither Hillary Clinton nor Donald Trump is the clear favorite as the two major-party candidates for the White House go head-to-head in their crucial first debate Monday. If Clinton, the Democratic nominee, possesses deep Washington experience and in-depth knowledge of the issues, she lacks what supporters of her Republican rival see as his authenticity. The two candidates have been laying into each other for a year but have never appeared face-to-face on the same stage, just strides apart.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 07:09:46', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/debaters-trump-clinton-both-strengths-weaknesses-070946170.html', '', 4),
(157, 'Pope to meet families of Nice attack victims', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/pope-meet-families-nice-attack-victims-040446807.html"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/hUGEcJBbDYRhZcSY2u1Sug--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/90df152cfec453228847b293b05e3fef5265a4c0.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Pope Francis will meet with 180 people who were wounded, or left traumatised or bereaved by the July 14 Bastille Day attack in Nice which claimed 86 lives" align="left" title="Pope Francis will meet with 180 people who were wounded, or left traumatised or bereaved by the July 14 Bastille Day attack in Nice which claimed 86 lives" border="0" /></a>Pope Francis will on Saturday hold a multi-faith meeting of grieving relatives and survivors of an attack in France in July when a jihadist ploughed his truck into a crowd in Nice. Last month the Argentine pontiff met with French President Francois Hollande to offer his support and condolences to a country which has been rocked by a series of deadly attacks since early 2015. While speaking out against violent acts carried out in the name of any god, Francis this week reminded the West that there were parts of the world being flattened by fighting.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 04:04:46', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/pope-meet-families-nice-attack-victims-040446807.html', '', 4),
(158, 'Momentum: Pro-Corbyn group upsetting Labour party', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/momentum-pro-corbyn-group-upsetting-labour-party-032437572.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/LmFFBEb8p9GgPIanUqUxtg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/aefade5dddf4ecb3f87886ee55a806855f3b9a4b.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Supporters of Jeremy Corbyn hold up signs at a Black, Asian and Minority Ethnic (BAME) rally in north London organised by &#039;Jeremy for Labour&#039; on August 15, 2016" align="left" title="Supporters of Jeremy Corbyn hold up signs at a Black, Asian and Minority Ethnic (BAME) rally in north London organised by &#039;Jeremy for Labour&#039; on August 15, 2016" border="0" /></a>Dismissed as a shadowy group of Marxist infiltrators or hailed as a grassroots movement energising left-wing politics, the campaign organisation Momentum, which backs Labour leader Jeremy Corbyn, is unsettling British politics. Momentum grew out of Corbyn&#039;s campaign to lead the main opposition Labour party last year, and now counting 18,000 members, has been vigorously supporting his efforts to fight off a leadership challenge by Owen Smith. Leftist stalwart Corbyn, 67, is expected to be reconfirmed as leader on Saturday at the party conference in Liverpool.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 03:24:37', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/momentum-pro-corbyn-group-upsetting-labour-party-032437572.html', '', 4),
(159, 'Feds push back on states targeting Planned Parenthood funds', 'WICHITA, Kan. (AP) — The Obama administration has proposed barring states and other recipients of federal family planning grants from placing their own eligibility restrictions on where the money can go, which would undermine the efforts of 13 Republican-led states to prevent such money from going to Planned Parenthood.', '2016-09-24 14:37:40', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/feds-push-back-states-targeting-planned-parenthood-funds-143508739.html', '', 5),
(160, 'The 10 Healthiest Places to Live in America', 'From Hawaii to New Hampshire, here\'s where to move for your health.', '2016-09-24 09:38:39', '0', 0, 0, 'http://abcnews.go.com/Health/10-healthiest-places-live-america/story?id=42317210', '', 5),
(161, 'Medically unfit\' Fury out of Klitschko rematch', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/medically-unfit-fury-klitschko-rematch-093425332--box.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/olflQavQv9bxdxE4LAWUcQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_ZA/News/Reuters/2016-09-24T093425Z_1007960001_LYNXNPEC8N06D_RTROPTP_2_OZASP-UK-BOXING-FURY-KLITSCHKO.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="Tyson Fury &amp; Wladimir Klitschko Head-to-Head Press Conference" align="left" title="Tyson Fury &amp; Wladimir Klitschko Head-to-Head Press Conference" border="0" /></a>Next month&#039;s world heavyweight title rematch between champion Tyson Fury and Ukrainian Vladimir Klitschko was called off on Friday for a second time with the Briton ruled &quot;medically unfit&quot;. The fight was due to be held on Oct. 29 in Manchester, having been originally postponed in July when Fury suffered an ankle injury. &quot;Tyson has this week been declared medically unfit to fight,&quot; his promoters Hennessy Sports said in a statement without elaborating.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 09:34:25', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/medically-unfit-fury-klitschko-rematch-093425332--box.html', '', 5),
(162, '"We don\'t need to grow more food to cut hunger in Africa" - activist', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/dont-grow-more-food-cut-hunger-africa-activist-082332897.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/3Ji9UCnFAg0s8imdVmrHjw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_ZA/News/Reuters/2016-09-24T082332Z_1007970001_LYNXNPEC8N055_RTROPTP_2_OZATP-US-AFRICA-FARMING-HUNGER.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="A Malawian trader counts money as he sells maize near the capital Lilongwe" align="left" title="A Malawian trader counts money as he sells maize near the capital Lilongwe" border="0" /></a>By Alex Whiting TURIN, Italy (Thomson Reuters Foundation) - As a young university student of agriculture, Edie Mukiibi believed the latest hybrid seeds which promised bumper crops were the answer to improving the lot of maize farmers in his part of Uganda.    He persuaded many to buy the seeds, while working part-time promoting them in Kiboga district in central Uganda.     But the consequences were &quot;terrible&quot;, he said. When I went back to talk with the farmers I could feel their pain,&quot; Mukiibi said.     Even worse, the new crops could not be grown with any other crops, so the farmers were left with nothing to fall back on except the bills they had run up for the pesticides, herbicides and fertilisers the maize required, he said.    &quot;This is when I started working with farmers ... to diversify (their) farming,&quot; said Mukiibi, now vice president of Slow Food International, a grassroots movement of farmers, chefs, activists and academics campaigning to improve the quality of food and the lives of producers.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 08:23:32', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/dont-grow-more-food-cut-hunger-africa-activist-082332897.html', '', 5),
(163, 'U.S. presidential contest takes center stage for investors', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/u-presidential-contest-takes-center-stage-investors-013529125--finance.html"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/s9oNseP1Vx.ov6iMBlf3gg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-09-24T030013Z_3_LYNXNPEC8M1DO_RTROPTP_2_BRITAIN-EU-INVESTMENT-BANKS.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="A Wall Street sign outside the New York Stock Exchange" align="left" title="A Wall Street sign outside the New York Stock Exchange" border="0" /></a>Who becomes the next U.S. president will be a primary focus for Wall Street next week and beyond, starting on Monday with the first debate between candidates Hillary Clinton and Donald Trump. While the White House race has so far had little discernible effect on the market, that may soon change as polls show a tightening race. Clinton&#039;s once-comfortable lead in opinion polls has evaporated, and with just over six weeks until Election Day, some investors see a toss-up contest creating volatility in certain sectors, including health insurers, drugmakers and industrials.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-24 03:00:13', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/u-presidential-contest-takes-center-stage-investors-013529125--finance.html', '', 5),
(164, 'Cowboys, heat and rain: \'Magnificent Seven\' talk challenging shoot', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/cowboys-heat-rain-magnificent-seven-talk-challenging-shoot-220223200.html"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/QVw9S7uYWj9I2GxC2l8qcg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-09-23T220223Z_1_LYNXNPEC8M1EX_RTROPTP_2_FILMFESTIVAL-TIFF-MAGNIFICENTSEVEN.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="nThe cast poses on the red carpet for the film &quot;The Magnificent Seven&quot; during the 41st Toronto International Film Festival (TIFF), in Toronto" align="left" title="nThe cast poses on the red carpet for the film &quot;The Magnificent Seven&quot; during the 41st Toronto International Film Festival (TIFF), in Toronto" border="0" /></a>By Piya Sinha-Roy LOS ANGELES (Reuters) - Bringing the American Wild West to life was no easy task, just ask the cast of &quot;The Magnificent Seven,&quot; who endured scorching heat and torrential rain in wool costumes in the Louisiana summer. &quot;We had a lot of lightning, thunder issues where we had to shut (production) down, but the heat was just constant,&quot; Denzel Washington, who plays bounty hunter Sam Chisholm, told Reuters. &quot;The Magnificent Seven,&quot; a remake of the 1960 classic, is directed by Antoine Fuqua and opens in theaters on Friday.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 22:02:23', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/cowboys-heat-rain-magnificent-seven-talk-challenging-shoot-220223200.html', '', 5),
(165, 'Fury pulls out of Klitschko rematch through injury', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/fury-pulls-klitschko-rematch-injury-220110837--box.html"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/YnVBkQXenIQ6OL6pmXky1w--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-09-23T220110Z_1006980001_LYNXNPEC8M1EW_RTROPTP_2_CSPORTS-US-BOXING-FURY-KLITSCHKO.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="Hughie Fury v Fred Kassi WBO Intercontinental Heavyweight Title" align="left" title="Hughie Fury v Fred Kassi WBO Intercontinental Heavyweight Title" border="0" /></a>BERLIN (Reuters) - The world heavyweight title rematch between champion Tyson Fury and Ukrainian Vladimir Klitschko on Oct. 29 has been called off for a second time with the Briton ruled &quot;medically unfit&quot;. &quot;Tyson has this week been declared medically unfit to fight,&quot; Fury&#039;s promoters Hennessy Sports said in a brief statement on Friday. &quot;Medical specialists have advised that the condition is too severe to allow him to participate in the rematch and that he will require treatment before going back into the ring.&quot; (Reporting by Karolos Grohmann; Editing by Tony Jimenez)</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 22:01:10', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/fury-pulls-klitschko-rematch-injury-220110837--box.html', '', 5),
(166, 'Boxing-\'Medically unfit\' Fury out of Klitschko rematch', '* Heavyweight fight called off for second time * Champion Fury\'s condition is "too severe" (Adds quotes, details) BERLIN, Sept 23 (Reuters) - Next month\'s world heavyweight title rematch between champion Tyson Fury and Ukrainian Vladimir Klitschko was called off on Friday for a second time with the Briton ruled "medically unfit". The fight was due to be held on Oct. 29 in Manchester, having been originally postponed in July when Fury suffered an ankle injury. "Tyson has this week been declared medically unfit to fight," his promoters Hennessy Sports said in a statement without elaborating.', '2016-09-23 22:01:02', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/boxing-medically-unfit-fury-klitschko-rematch-220102869--box.html', '', 5),
(167, 'FDA approves Amgen\'s copy of AbbVie arthritis drug Humira', 'The U.S. Food and Drug Administration on Friday approved Amgen Inc\'s biosimilar version of AbbVie\'s top-selling arthritis drug, Humira. The drug, Amjevita, known also as adalimumab-atto, was approved to treat rheumatoid arthritis, psoriatic arthritis, Crohn\'s disease, psoriasis and other conditions. Amjevita is the fourth biosimilar to be approved by the FDA and is expected to be sold at a discount to the original drug.', '2016-09-23 21:51:34', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/fda-approves-amgens-cheaper-copy-arthritis-drug-humira-205018669--finance.html', '', 5),
(168, 'Boxing-Fury pulls out of Klitschko rematch through injury', 'BERLIN, Sept 23 (Reuters) - The world heavyweight title rematch between champion Tyson Fury and Ukrainian Vladimir Klitschko on Oct. 29 has been called off for a second time with the Briton ruled "medically unfit". "Tyson has this week been declared medically unfit to fight," Fury\'s promoters Hennessy Sports said in a brief statement on Friday. "Medical specialists have advised that the condition is too severe to allow him to participate in the rematch and that he will require treatment before going back into the ring." (Reporting by Karolos Grohmann; Editing by Tony Jimenez)', '2016-09-23 21:39:05', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/boxing-fury-pulls-klitschko-rematch-injury-213905444--box.html', '', 5),
(169, 'Serious injuries rare at popular obstacle courses', 'By Madeline Kennedy (Reuters Health) - Obstacle course runs like Tough Mudder and Warrior Dash are becoming more popular and are relatively safe for participants, a Canadian study suggests. Only about 1 percent of participants are injured during these races, and most of the injuries are minor and only require first aid, the researchers write in Emergency Medicine Journal. Obstacle course runs can be anywhere from 3 miles long to a full marathon.', '2016-09-23 21:04:26', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/serious-injuries-rare-popular-obstacle-courses-210426390--spt.html', '', 5),
(170, '6 Portland health providers give $21.5M for homeless housing', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/6-portland-health-providers-21-5m-homeless-housing-201936949.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/lRdMyTCTBKgBoyJJbBHiAg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/cb3bb4205a7e483a96ee858be8857364.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="FILE - In this Aug. 10, 2016 file photo, Deitra Schmer watches as her granddaughter, Andrea Brown, brushes her hair and grandson Adrian Atkinson, right, look on in Schmer&#039;s tent in a homeless encampment along the Springwater Corridor bike and pedestrian trail in Portland, Ore. Five major hospitals in Portland and a low-income, nonprofit health plan are donating a combined $21.5 million to build nearly 400 housing units for the city&#039;s homeless population, Friday, Sept. 23, 2016. (AP Photo/Gillian Flaccus,File)" align="left" title="FILE - In this Aug. 10, 2016 file photo, Deitra Schmer watches as her granddaughter, Andrea Brown, brushes her hair and grandson Adrian Atkinson, right, look on in Schmer&#039;s tent in a homeless encampment along the Springwater Corridor bike and pedestrian trail in Portland, Ore. Five major hospitals in Portland and a low-income, nonprofit health plan are donating a combined $21.5 million to build nearly 400 housing units for the city&#039;s homeless population, Friday, Sept. 23, 2016. (AP Photo/Gillian Flaccus,File)" border="0" /></a>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) — Five major hospitals in Portland, Oregon, and a nonprofit health care plan said Friday they will donate a combined $21.5 million toward the construction of nearly 400 housing units for the city&#039;s burgeoning homeless and low-income population — a move hailed by national housing advocates as the largest private investment of its kind in the nation.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 21:03:55', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/6-portland-health-providers-21-5m-homeless-housing-201936949.html', '', 5),
(171, 'Patients’ time at home after a stroke varies by hospital', 'By Lisa Rapaport (Reuters Health) - Stroke survivors may spend more time at home – as opposed to a nursing home or a hospital – if they were treated at a place that handles a lot of stroke patients or that’s located in a rural area, a U.S. study suggests. Patients treated at smaller hospitals also tended to spend more days at home after a stroke, the study also found. “Home-time after stroke varied depending on where patients were hospitalized and in what type of hospital,” said study leader Emily O’Brian of Duke University in Durham, North Carolina.', '2016-09-23 20:47:39', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/patients-time-home-stroke-varies-hospital-204739043.html', '', 5),
(172, 'Allergists Warn Against Using \'DIY EpiPen\'', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/allergists-warn-against-using-diy-epipen-195940170.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/SGB0QM3qVkpGQN.cGui7bA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/gma/us.abcnews.go.com/GTY_EpiPen_hb_160825_16x9_992.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Allergists Warn Against Using &#039;DIY EpiPen&#039;" align="left" title="Allergists Warn Against Using &#039;DIY EpiPen&#039;" border="0" /></a>Online tutorials that teach people how to make their own EpiPens have been watched by tens of thousands, but experts warn that using a homemade injector could be dangerous. However, Dr. Lolita McDavid, pediatrician and medical director of child advocacy and protection at University Hospitals Rainbow Babies &amp; Children’s Hospital, said even as a trained physician she would never use a DIY epi-injector on a family member. McDavid pointed out that in one video online the instructor didn&#039;t even sterilize the vial before filling the syringe, meaning it could possibly cause infection if used.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 20:00:05', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/allergists-warn-against-using-diy-epipen-195940170.html', '', 5),
(173, 'Officials Investigate Leprosy Case in California', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/officials-investigate-leprosy-case-california-170005729.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/BqHQyiFLVrKpjE927cHGkA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/gma/us.abcnews.go.com/GettyImages-128580565_16x9_992.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Officials Investigate Leprosy Case in California" align="left" title="Officials Investigate Leprosy Case in California" border="0" /></a>California health officials reported on Thursday that a child in Jurupa Valley, California, has been diagnosed with leprosy and another child is suspected of having the disease. Leprosy, also called Hansen&#039;s disease, is rare in the U.S., according to the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services. There were 175 new cases of the disease reported in 2014, the most recent data available. The Riverside County Health Department has not listed a source or suspected source of the disease, but leprosy can remain in the body for three to 10 years before symptoms develop, according to the HHS.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 20:00:05', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/officials-investigate-leprosy-case-california-170005729.html', '', 5),
(174, 'Endo International CEO steps down, Campanelli named successor', 'Endo International Plc said Chief Executive Rajiv De Silva had stepped down and would be replaced by generics division head Paul Campanelli, as the drugmaker grapples with a large debt load and mounting pressure on some of its drug prices. Endo\'s shares rose as much as 18 percent to $23.98 on Friday as the company also maintained its full-year profit and revenue forecasts. Campanelli joined Endo in 2015 following the company\'s $8-billion acquisition of generic drugs maker Par Pharmaceutical, where he was CEO since 2012.', '2016-09-23 19:36:13', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/endo-international-ceo-steps-down-campanelli-named-successor-141537668--finance.html', '', 5),
(175, 'Adult, larval insecticides pack deadly punch to mosquitoes, Zika: U.S.', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/adult-larval-insecticides-pack-deadly-punch-mosquitoes-zika-190818048.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/Q9HRLsNJvfuDmTBXelFduQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-09-23T190853Z_2_LYNXNPEC8M19B_RTROPTP_2_HEALTH-ZIKA-USA.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="An airplane carrying a banner asking people to use insect repellent to avoid the Zika virus, flies over Miami" align="left" title="An airplane carrying a banner asking people to use insect repellent to avoid the Zika virus, flies over Miami" border="0" /></a>(Reuters) - The unprecedented aerial spraying of products that kill both adult mosquitoes as well as their larvae delivered a &quot;1-2 punch&quot; that has stopped direct transmission of the Zika virus in the Wynwood section of Miami, U.S. and Florida health officials said on Friday. The trendy Miami neighborhood in June became the first neighborhood in the continental United States with a local outbreak of Zika, a mosquito-borne virus that can cause severe birth defects in infected pregnant women. The U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention on Monday declared Wynwood free of Zika, saying there had been no cases of infection with the virus there in the past 45 days.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 19:08:53', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/adult-larval-insecticides-pack-deadly-punch-mosquitoes-zika-190818048.html', '', 5),
(176, 'With U.S. drone rules set, firms race for flight data', '<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/ups-launches-u-drone-test-flights-urgent-medical-122330854--sector.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/lA7Zdfr8q3O7UpwXc5GC0A--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-09-23T160701Z_2_LYNXNPEC8M0QH_RTROPTP_2_UNITED-PARCEL-DRONES-DELIVERY.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="A drone, made by CyPhy Works, carries a UPS package on Children&#039;s Island off the coast of Beverly" align="left" title="A drone, made by CyPhy Works, carries a UPS package on Children&#039;s Island off the coast of Beverly" border="0" /></a>UPS&#039;s test flight was handled by drone maker CyPhy Works, in which it owns a stake. &quot;The technology for drones is there and it&#039;s moving extremely fast,&quot; said CyPhy founder Helen Greiner. The UPS-CyPhy test comes amid a burst of U.S. drone activity, including companies focusing on package delivery.</p><br clear="all"/>', '2016-09-23 18:52:17', '0', 0, 0, 'http://news.yahoo.com/ups-launches-u-drone-test-flights-urgent-medical-122330854--sector.html', '', 5);
